                    <div id="page-content">
                        

<div style="text-align: right;"><div class="page-rate-widget-box"><span class="rate-points">rating:&nbsp;<span class="number prw54353">+14</span></span><span class="rateup btn btn-default"><a title="I like it" href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.modules.PageRateWidgetModule.listeners.rate(event, 1)">+</a></span><span class="ratedown btn btn-default"><a title="I don't like it" href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.modules.PageRateWidgetModule.listeners.rate(event, -1)">&#8211;</a></span><span class="cancel btn btn-default"><a title="Cancel my vote" href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.modules.PageRateWidgetModule.listeners.cancelVote(event)">x</a></span></div></div>
<p><strong>Author Name:</strong> I'm Max.</p>
<p><strong>Writings #:</strong> 3/5</p>
<p><strong>Likes:</strong> Long walks in my room.</p>
<p><strong>Dislikes:</strong> Children playing on construction equipment.</p>
<p><strong>Birthday:</strong> Today.</p>
<p><strong>Security Fault:</strong> Lack of hand rails.</p>
<p><strong>Taupe:</strong> Color.</p>
<h2 id="toc0"><span>All my gosh darn SCPs</span></h2>
<div class="list-pages-box">    

<table class="wiki-content-table">
<tr>
<th>SCP</th>
<th>Created</th>
<th>Rating</th>
<th>Comments</th>
<th>Length</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/scp-2881">SCP-2881</a></td>
<td><span class="odate time_1437723875 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">24 Jul 2015 07:44</span></td>
<td>386</td>
<td>44</td>
<td>3468</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/scp-2580">SCP-2580</a></td>
<td><span class="odate time_1444601198 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">11 Oct 2015 22:06</span></td>
<td>88</td>
<td>17</td>
<td>4624</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/scp-2446">SCP-2446</a></td>
<td><span class="odate time_1457295742 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">06 Mar 2016 20:22</span></td>
<td>70</td>
<td>13</td>
<td>5566</td>
</tr>
</table>

    
    
    
    </div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">SCP-2881</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">The&nbsp;Tree&nbsp;You&nbsp;Cannot&nbsp;Climb</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>The first day the <a href="/short-works-contest">Short Works Contest</a> was announced, I looked out the window and thought &quot;what could be an SCP, that tree maybe? What can you do with trees? You climb them. What if you couldn’t climb a tree?&quot; and the rest is history. This actually just barely ended up in the top quartile of the contest, but I put that down largely to having been posted within the first hour of the contest.</p>
<p>This was pretty quick to write, with most of the edits coming in about the ending. The tree in the photo is visible from my window, and that’s about it. Of course, I do want to write something to dive further into what it is/does, but that could subtract from the mystique. For anyone curious, my headcanon is that inside are <span style="background:#000000; color:#000000;">desert cannibals.</span></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">SCP-2580</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Father-Daughter&nbsp;Project</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>I made this because I had a model rocket, and I wanted to use it in an image. I guess that sort of worked out. The image it got seemed to work out well enough. I like the idea of an anomaly-creator having a kid, and just using their skills in normal situations and I think that that kind of thing is done alright there.</p>
<p>The image was not, in fact, drawn by a child, but was all me. Crossed-out sun was a legitimate mistake on my part, as were the planets on the other side coming in through the scan. Its inclusion was (I think) because I believed in the importance of images to engage a reader in an SCP, which I still believe in. Text is boring, but stock photos are similarly so. If you want to get that lot out, you gotta put that little bit in, if you know what I’m saying. Had I the skill, I probably would have put a map or scatter plot into the next one, but I didn’t.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">SCP-2446</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Mobile&nbsp;Task&nbsp;Force&nbsp;Lambda-5&nbsp;(&quot;White&nbsp;Rabbits&quot;)</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>This article was technically finished pretty quickly, and then for about two weeks I concentrated just on ironing out any and all kinks. This was the kingpin for my team’s entry into the <a href="/mobile-task-force-contest">Mobile Task Force Contest</a>, so it needed that polish, which I think it got. It doesn’t answer its questions, but that’s a part of the design for the contest.</p>
<p>I don’t believe that the Lambda-5 series is done. Someday, maybe.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
